tion bar to disappear)\n\n2. The changes are all in the frontend Phaser3 app (`a
pps/phaser3/src/city-builder/` and related files). No DB, API, or shared type ch
anges.\n\n3. `make lint` has many errors, but they all seem to be in Go backend 
code and unrelated to this PR\'s TypeScript changes. They look like pre-existing
issues (missing imports, wire issues, etc.).\n\n4. `make check-docs` passes.\n\n
5. No `.design-assets.txt` or `.figma-links.txt` content (both empty files), so 
no specific UI design assets to compare against.\n\n6. The diff shows:\n   - `Bu
ildingActionBar.ts`: Added `MoveConfirm` and `MoveCancel` button types, added `m
oveConfirmCallbacks`, added `createMoveConfirmButtons()` and `showMoveConfirm()`
methods\n   - `UIManager.ts`: Added `showMoveConfirmBar()` and `hideMoveConfirmB
ar()` methods\n   - `CityPlugin.ts`: Modified `startRelocate()` to show move con
firm bar via UIManager instead of Building handling it internally. The confirm/c
ancel logic was moved from Building.ts to CityPlugin.ts\n   - `Building.ts`: Rem
oved the hardcoded action bar (`actionBar`, `actionBarCallbacks`, `showActionBar
()`, `hideActionBar()`, `showMoveActionBar()`, `createImageButton()`, `setAction
BarCallbacks()`, `BuildingActionCallbacks` interface). Added getter methods for 
drag positions and position validator. Removed action bar calls from state handl
ers.\n   - `IsometricCityMap.ts`: Removed `BuildingActionCallbacks` import and `
setActionBarCallbacks()` method.\n\nLet me now check for tests and documentation
. I should look at:\n- Are there unit tests for the modified TS files?\n- Is the
module documented in `docs/modules/`?\n- Are there any Gherkin tests?\n\nLet me 
also look at the specific issue. The PR removes the hardcoded action bar from Bu
ilding.ts and delegates it to the UIManager. This seems correct architecturally.
\n\nLet me check the existing tests and docs.',
